# Release Artifacts

When creating a GitHub release, **always build and attach the binary artifacts** before considering the release complete.

## Android releases (`android-v*`)

1. Build the debug APK: `cd android && ./gradlew assembleDebug`
2. Upload to the release: `gh release upload <tag> android/app/build/outputs/apk/debug/openRS_v*.apk`
3. The APK filename follows the pattern `openRS_v{version}-staging-debug.apk`

## Firmware releases (`fw-usb-v*`, `fw-pro-v*`)

1. Clean build for the target: `cd firmware && rm -rf .build/<target>/wican-fw && bash build.sh --target <usb|pro>`
2. Upload all flash files: `gh release upload <tag> firmware/release/openrs-fw-<target>_v*.bin firmware/release/bootloader_<target>.bin firmware/release/partition-table_<target>.bin firmware/release/ota_data_initial_<target>.bin`
3. Include SHA256 hashes from `firmware/release/BUILD_MANIFEST_<target>.json` in the release notes

## Checklist

A release is not complete until:
- [ ] Binary artifacts are built from the tagged commit
- [ ] Artifacts are uploaded to the GitHub release
- [ ] Older pre-releases for the same component are demoted (see `release-lifecycle.mdc`)
